caption: I had the Steak Frites and it was absolutely delicious! Steak was a perfect medium well and the sauce was to die for! And let me tell you about these fries, it didn't make no damn sense for them to be that good!!! They are a MUST get every time! The ambiance is very nice, i like this place. Must try

I ordered the crab cakes and shrimp never got the shrimp left hungry the sweet tea tasted as if they strapped the bottom of the container ... We felt as though they were rushing us out because we didn't"fit" in.
Professional, courteous & amazing food/drinks/service! Thanks ladies and gentlemen. You all deserve an applause 👏👏
Love this place.  Was disappointed in the Valentines pre set menu, but I totally understand.

Great dining experience with excellent, quick service. Reservations were easy to make and we were seated immediately at the reserved time. The food was good for the price and service. We had the crab cakes, calamari, braised short ribs and the special of the night lamb chops. I would definitely go back for a good meal with excellent service.
One of my favorite in the city.

We normally LOVE this place and chose it for our 1 meal in freedom! After waiting over 30 minutes with a confirmed reservation, we were told that the kitchen was backed up and we still were not being seated. The couple seated 35 minutes prior still only had waters and menus at their table. Sorry Bistro Aix! Would've LOVED a meal in freedom....

Went the day before Valentine's Day... no mention of a Valentine's Day menu on their website. Arrived and got a Valentine's Day menu, which not only was very limited and didn't include anything I really wanted, but every item was $2 more than usual. Mussels and Crab cake apps were very good, but the shrimp with pasta main was bland... the tomato cream sauce had zero flavor. Adding to the problem, the server never asked me if I wanted pepper or grated cheese (both which was needed) and there was no salt or pepper on the table due to Covid. Ordered a piece of cake for dessert... a small sliver, although very good, was $12.  I spent a lot of money for an unmemorable meal and felt as though I was gouged. I probably would not return.

One of our favorite restaurants in Jacksonville. The food and service are always top notch.  Tonight the service was incredibly exceptional. Our waitress, Jessi, was professional, friendly, attentive and just a complete delight. If you come here, be sure to request her service. Just not on a night when we're there!

I eat out often, and never leave reviews. I actually wish I had cancelled, and just let them take the $40 cancellation fee to save the other $60. Great ambiance, beautiful decor,  fresh taste, yet the the food is definitely overpriced for the portion size. UNLESS YOUR ON A DIET! (I’m not) After a long day, was very hungry, and excited to try this place out. I went in hungry...and sadly I left hungry. $100 later....

I’m very unsure how this place has such great reviews. We came on the Friday before Valentine’s Day, and honestly could have gotten better service at an Applebee’s. We were treated so poorly from start to finish, and the restaurant was not even close to full capacity. Even with a reservation (that was booked 3 weeks out), we waited 30 minutes to get a table. It seemed fine at first, but after waiting close to an hour for our appetizer, I realized that our waitress just did not care about our dining experience, nor did the management who delivered our long awaited crab cakes. Our waitress hardly came to check on us, and there were multiple times when both my water glass and drink glasses were empty and I had to try to get her attention. When our food finally came, you could tell that our entrees had been under the warmer for quite some time, as the plates were hot and the food was very dry. The best part was, after waiting so long for our food, I had to ask for silverware because in that hour and a half’s time of us waiting, no one had the foresight to think that maybe we wouldn’t want to eat our $35 a plate meal with our hands! We were offered no apologies from the waitress, nor did the management try to remedy our experience. They were clearly aware of the situation, as we caught them talking and looking straight at us, but no one cared to acknowledge our ruined Valentine’s experience. I would not recommend this place for any type of celebration. Clearly, they can’t handle it.
Great food and great atmosphere

A very limited valentines day dinner menu, waitress was average at best. Never asked if we wanted a 2nd drink, never asked for coffee refill. Split the check without asking how we were handling the bill....
Awesome food,  delicious cocktails.  I love the ambiance.  Great attention to detail.  Management is always close at hand ensuring an excellent experience.
The food and service was great, a little overpriced

Bistro X is a San Marco staple for date nights or special celebrations. The ambiance is beautiful, the staff is extremely welcoming and the food is consistently delicious. We always start with a charcuterie plate and the tuna tartare. You really can’t go wrong with any entree here but if they have Chilean sea bass on special, I highly recommend. And finally, don’t forget dessert! The chocolate mousse cake is rich and will top off the evening perfectly.
Always a fabulous meal at Bistro AIX. Braised short ribs deliciousness.
Delicious well prepared meals, great salads and fabulous desserts. Service was impeccable. Plenty of outdoor seating too.  A wonderful experience!
service is always timely even when they have a full house. the staff was helpful and kind.

I don't usually write reviews, but after dining here last night again, I just felt like I had to. This was our third time eating here, and every time has been amazing. First off, we showed up an hour earlier than our reservation time, and they accommodated us no problem. The food is SO GOOD!! Every thing we've eaten here has been amazing. The escargot is to die for. I'm impressed with their social distancing and covid protocols, more so than any other indoor restaurant I've been to. The tables are appropriately distanced (there are tables not in use in between each group). They also clean the tables and chairs with a special spray/ UV light device in between every group, I've never seen this before. All employees were appropriately masked. And finally the service is so on point. We felt extremely well taken care of by all the wait staff, and the manager even came to check in on us once or twice. Definitely our favorite place to eat in San Marco, probably in all of Jacksonville!!
This is where I had my wedding proposal. Everything was done so beautiful. The food was good.
Great environment,amazing quality food and drinks! Definitely a place to bring your lady in a suit and her finest outfit.
Delicious and great atmosphere!
Best French Onion soup in Jacksonville.

The four of us dined here before the Holidays Pops Symphony.  Wow! Service was solid...all employees masked up and could see them sanitizing tables and chairs in between guests.  Staggered tables for dining.  The food was really on point...we tried a couple appetizers-Calamari, as well as their meat/cheese board offering.  We each had a different entree and thumbs up for all of them.  The atmosphere was intimate and subdued, which fostered good conversation.  We will be returning soon!
So good.
Beautiful atmosphere and very kind staff.
Very friendly staff and wonderful food.
great little place, not cheap but fantastic food and atmosphere
Great food great service.
Absolutely amazing cuisine and beverages pleasant atmosphere staff is polite and well knowledgeable. Had a terrific time. Definitely five stars

The waiter was great...I went with my date based on the online information that it was worth the trip for the escargot.  So off we went.  Nice wine list, very relaxing atmosphere.  Ordered the escargot.  Overall the best i have ever had.  The online claims were correct.  Then i ordered the Mushroom Parmesan Rigatoni with truffle oil.  I asked the waiter specifically if he knew if it was real truffle oil or the fake stuff.   He replied "oh its the real stuff and it is worked into the sauce.  My date ordered Seared Scallops and asparagus risotto with a wine reduction.  My meal was a heavy cream parmesan sauce with some mushrooms, regular brown button mushrooms.  The sauce was so heavy with cream that you could only taste a little parmesan.  Definitely NO TRUFFLE OIL. (can't fault the waiter because that maybe what he was told).  If their was a "truffle oil" used then it was the very cheap stuff that loses its flavor quickly.  If it was a basic "Mushroom Parmesan Cream Sauce Rigatoni" then I would have been less critical.  My dates meal:  the Scallops were seared to perfection; great job on that.  The risotto was empty of flavor and the Asparagus was mushy and tasteless as well.  As for the "Wine Reduction" ; it was a balsamic glaze not a wine reduction.  It might have been a store bought brand.  I say that because it lacked the delicate sweet bite of a true balsamic reduction.  If you want a nice wine list and some AMAZING escargot then by all means go.  As for the rest....not impressed at all.   Especially for the prices...$24 for mine (no truffle oil); $35 for my date (lack luster flavor).
French food at this location - excellent. i can say this place does it for me. i will be bringing family next time. the bill was decent.
french food and the setting at this spot is excellent. I love visiting here. There was fast and courteous service. The bill was decent. Atmosphere is similar to a cafe in San Jose I loved.
Great food and relaxing setting. Eaten there 2-3 times this week. Moderately priced so you're not sitting for a cheap meal!
My favorite place for quality French food. Very filling. Looking forward to coming back with my coworkers. The bill was decent for the quality. Ambience is similar to Fresno's scene.

One of my preferred spots for delicious French food. great location to meet with friends. i think i might become a regular. this place has an awesome atmosphere. similar to a cafe in las vegas i liked.
Excellent!
Fantastic place! I had the best filet steak ever! We had big party so wait time was a little while but definitely worth the wait! Thank you to the owner for coming up to us! 🍹
Food was very average. Not worth the price in my opinion
The service was good but the food was underwhelming for the price

This is the best place in Jax if you want to experience great food and excellent customer service. I am the first in my Family to graduate with my Masters Degree. We decided to hold our black tie event here as a family. I have been treated like a king. I love this place!💙 Thank you for making this experience wonderful for me. Mr. Golden
Great place. Real classy. And a good place for a first date
It’s worth a visit. The food is amazing. Don’t forget desert
Food was good, but over priced and service wasn't very good.

Excellent dinner tonight. Service is top notch & the food was delicious. A nice variety of wine to choose from. The Escargot was as good as advertised! Yellow snapper was terrific!! Perfectly prepared. The Cioppino was delicious with lots of tasty morsels. The sauce was very tasty as were the shrimp & fish. Dessert: the crembulee was perfect! Thanks Imad for making the evening special.. BTW: safe place to relax & dine! Please support this iconic place!!
Nice restaurant. Good food and good service. The brussel sprouts were really good. I liked the outside dining area. The piano music was nice.
french food at this place - very good. Fell in love with this place from the 1st taste. The staff was friendly and sociable. Bring your hunger - portions are filling.

The escargot is the best I have ever had! They suggested a Barolo wine that was amazing! Everyone was delighted with their choices and the service was 5 star! This is one of my favorite date night dinner spots in Jacksonville!
Ok spot for delicious French food. I'll return with my coworkers.
My preferred place for delicious french food. food was so tasty. looking forward to coming back with my friends. it has a nice feel to it. i can see why they have a lot of positive reviews.
One of my favorite places for delicious French food. Looking forward to coming back with my coworkers.

My favorite place for tasty french food. Great place to relax, people watch, eat good food or all the above.  I'll return with my friends. The bill was average for the menu. I see why this place has a lot of great reviews.

giving a 5 star review to one of my favorite restaurants that I've been going to for years because I love their food . however , as I like to go in for lunch on a early day. any get a couple Blue Goose Martinins,  I was surprised they had gone up to $ 19.50 . so for a couple Martinins I'm looking at over 40 dollars . come on , really ?

They are open and I appreciate them following through with the mandatory masks. They have hand sanitizer for u and they are taking reservations and keeping the restaurant spaced out. There are some restaurants that are putting money over safety and they are not. Good food and great service, thank you for opening safely during this difficult time.
French food and service here is excellent. Service is excellent even when they are busy. The bill won't shock you.
Delicious food and a good atmosphere in the evenings. Definitely recommend.
Excellent ambiental, very clean,food really good 👍
Our server was inexperienced. Steak and potato plate tasted chewy. Nice atmosphere.
Service was fabulous. Food was fantastic. Only issue the filet was over cooked and petite.

Very slow service. Took 15 minutes to even get water and another 25 minutes after that to get the two drinks we ordered (glass of wine and mixed drink). Unfortunately, no acknowledgement that everything was taking so long from the waitress which makes it seem like it’s expected? The couple next to us had their drinks comped and actually left because everything was taking so long. We stuck it out-  and the food was actually good. Had the special, Halibut. The quality of the food was definitely overshadowed by the poor service. Probably won’t be back as there are other places with similar/better food with quicker service.

Have been going here for YEARS, since it first opened. Ownership changed earlier this year, and the new owner is GREAT! The menu changed slightly, but the quality is still EXCELLENT. So often a change in ownership means a decline in quality, but not this time! Still absolutely delicious food with wonderful and friendly service.
Great place with amazing food and service.

I had some Salmon with a sweet soy glaze and it was pretty good. Small portion for that amount of money. I like the veggies that came with it. The waitress was really nice but the only thing is that we wasn't informed that there would be a 20% tip added to the bill. Even though we planned to tip, we would have been nice to give our own tip especially if the waitress/waiter didn't  do a good job. Luckily she did though.
Good ambiance great service, the food is mediocre at best . Ordered the fish aixues , too salty definitely not 4 star quality
